Cell.Text: There is always work for the Companions. But there is more personal task before me.
Of course, there is always work. My mind is someplace else, though.

Node.Caption: CR13QuestStartTopic: Is there any work to be done?

Cell.Text: Kodlak's final teaching. I think he was right about beastblood and Sovngarde. | I wish to cleanse myself that I might know glory in the afterlife.
I think that maybe Kodlak was right. As a werewolf, I can't be a good Nord. | I want to be clean, like he was, and go to Sovngarde when I finally die.

Node.Caption: CR13WellGoodLuckWithAllThat: This is a personal matter, and I leave it to you.

Cell.Text: I would be honored for you to accompany me, Harbinger.

Node.Caption: CR13WellLetsDoIt: I will help you cure yourself.

Cell.Text: [S] G|You still bear a head of the Glenmoril betrayers, yes? Then lead on, back to the Tomb of Ysramor. | My soul is now prepared.
[S] G|You still have one of the witch's heads. This is good. | Let's go to the Tomb. We can do the cleansing there.
[S] G|Aela said that the cleansing used a head from one of the witches of Glenmoril, yes? | A strange kind of ritual, but I won't mind killing those wretched things.
[S] G|Aela said we would need a Hagraven's head. I already have one of them, but she said it was a special kind. | And that you knew where to get more. Let's go find one!
[S] G|Lead on, to Ysgramor and glory.
[S] G|This is good. Could you show the way to the tomb again?

[S] <<Shared>> I... it's like waking up out of a dream. | I can breathe more deeply now. I can't smell your heart beating the way I used to. But my mind is... clear. | This is a great service you've done for me, Harbinger. I will not soon forget. | Now... I'd like to spend some time communing with Ysgramor. My soul is clean now. Perhaps he'll still welcome me when my time comes.

[S] <<Shared>> It's like relaxing into a warm mug of spiced mead. I'm losing aches I didn't know I had. | This is how a warrior should feel. Alive and aware. Not clouded with thoughts of the hunt. | Thank you for your help. I'm going to stay in the tomb for a while. My shame kept me out before, but now I want to see it.
